<subSubSection id="72A1650E0A130924379BFEB5C446FE4C" pageId="3" pageNumber="425" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3A0436850A130924379BFEB5C446FE4C" blockId="3.[151,1437,325,676]" pageId="3" pageNumber="425">
<emphasis id="08CFEA970A130924379BFEB5C74AFE97" bold="true" box="[151,274,325,351]" pageId="3" pageNumber="425">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="FDBB4D060A130924353AFEB7C4F2FEA8" authorityName="Li" authorityYear="2011" box="[566,682,327,352]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Phlogothamnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosus">
<emphasis id="08CFEA970A130924353AFEB7C4F2FEA8" box="[566,682,327,352]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="425">P. rugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from the latter by the shorter pygofer appendage and the more robust style.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
